Package: montyhall
Title: Simulates the Monty Hall Problem Game
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Santiago", "Nicotera Balatti", , "snicoter@asu.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides functions to simulate the Monty Hall Problem Game, a probability puzzle based on the TV show "Let's Make a Deal." The package allows users to play single games or simulate many repetitions, and compare the effectiveness of different strategies (staying vs switching doors).
Depends:
	dplyr
License: `use_mit_license()`, `use_gpl3_license()` or friends to pick a
    license
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
